cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the behavior of the IEEE 802.11 protocol at the Medium Access Control layer, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper includes a throughput analysis of the IEEE 802.11 protocol, which involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity and coding theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions multirate transmission, which is a common technique used in multimedia applications to adapt to varying network conditions. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper presents a multi-dimensional Markovian state transition model, which is a common tool used in systems and control theory. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper analyzes the throughput of the IEEE 802.11 protocol, which is a key performance metric for wireless networks.
